

	 
      i have said several things about paris already.  this next treasure cannot be left out.  this picture is of the second level of sainte chapelle.  the church was built in such a way that the second level, reserved only for the king, was completely surrounded by stained glass pieces.  on the main side, there is a beautiful rose window that entinces the imagination as to the work that it took to build it.  the rest of the level is covered in biblical scenery from top to bottom.  walking in there is walking into a palace of light.  at the right time, sunset, is the perfect time to capture the complete beauty of it all.  the soft light catches all the windows perfectly and drives the senses wild.  it is amazing. urlLink     urlLink   
     
    
